steps: Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease a baking sheet.. Combine bread crumbs, seafood seasoning, baking powder, parsley, mustard powder, and pepper in a medium bowl; set aside.. steps: Gather all ingredients.. Combine beaten egg, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, seafood seasoning, and hot pepper sauce in a large bowl. Stir in green onion and set aside.. Place crabmeat in a medium bowl and break up with a fork. Add milk, salt, and black pepper; toss to coat. Add saltine crackers and baking powder; toss lightly to combine. Add to egg mixture, stirring gently and being careful not to break apart crab lumps.. Scoop crab with a 1/3-cup measure and form into 8 patties. Place patties on a plate, cover, and refrigerate until firm, 1 to 8 hours.. Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Spray crab cakes on both sides with cooking spray and place in the air fryer basket.. Cook in the preheated air fryer for 5 minutes. Turn crab cakes over gently and continue cooking until crispy brown, about 5 minutes more.

steps: Melt butter in a large, heavy skillet over medium heat. Stir in onion; cook and stir until the onion has softened and turned translucent, about 5 minutes.. Stir in the celery, bell pepper, green onion, carrot, and garlic. Continue to cook and stir until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes more.. Season with 1 tablespoon parsley flakes, 2 teaspoons Creole seasoning, basil, pepper, dill weed, oregano, and thyme. Cook and stir until fragrant, 5 minutes more.. Transfer cooked vegetables to a large bowl; allow to cool for about 10 minutes. Set skillet aside for later use.. Stir the beaten eggs into the vegetables. Mix in the crabmeat and cracker crumbs with your hands, making sure not to break up the chunks of crab too much.. Shape the crab mixture into 12 small cakes.. Heat vegetable oil in the skillet over medium high heat.. Pan-fry the crab cakes in batches until golden brown on each side, about 3 minutes.. To make dipping sauce: Whisk together the mayonnaise, chile-garlic sauce, 2 teaspoon Creole seasoning, 2 teaspoon parsley flakes, and paprika.

steps: Whisk egg, mayonnaise, seafood seasoning, Dijon, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, lemon juice, and pepper together in a bowl.. name: Deviled Crab Cakes on Mixed Greens with Ginger-Citrus Vinaigrette
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely chopped celery'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely chopped red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dry mustard'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soft bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lemon zest'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'cooked crabmeat'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dry bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lemon, zested'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'minced fresh ginger root'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'jalapeno pepper, seeded and minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'vegetable oil for frying'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'mixed salad greens'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'avocados - peeled, pitted and sliced'}
steps: Melt the butter in a skillet over medium heat. Stir in the onion, and cook until softened and translucent, about 5 minutes. Add the celery and bell pepper; continue cooking until the vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in the mustard and cayenne pepper; cook 2 minutes. Scrape the mixture into a mixing bowl and refrigerate until cold.. Stir the mayonnaise into the chilled vegetable mixture along with the soft bread crumbs, 1 tablespoon lemon zest, parsley, and beaten egg. Stir until combined, then gently fold in the crab meat. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Pour the dry bread crumbs into a shallow bowl. Form the crab mixture into 8 cakes, 1/2 inch thick. Press the crab cakes into the bread crumbs one at a time until coated on all sides. Gently shake off excess crumbs, and place the crab cakes onto a plate. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 hour to overnight.. Prepare the vinaigrette by whisking 3/4 cup vegetable oil with the zest of 1 lemon, lemon juice, ginger, jalapeno, sugar, and salt. Store in the refrigerator until ready to use.. Heat the frying oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. While the oil is heating, toss the mixed salad greens with the vinaigrette in a mixing bowl, and divide onto 8 serving plates. Arrange the sliced avocado over the salads, and set aside.. Once the oil is shimmering with heat, fry the crab cakes until golden brown on each side, 2 to 3 minutes per side. Briefly drain on a paper towel-lined plate to rid the cakes of excess grease. Place a crab cake on top of each salad and serve immediately.

name: Fried Crab Cakes
ingredients: {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'seafood seasoning (such as Old Bay®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'yellow mustard'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'cooked lump crabmeat, drained'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'coconut oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'canned chipotle pepper in adobo sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'adobo sauce from chipotle peppers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}
steps: Mix 1/3 cup panko, egg, parsley, mayonnaise, seafood seasoning, and mustard together in a medium bowl. Gently fold in crabmeat. Form into 4 patties and coat with remaining panko.. Heat coconut oil in a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Fry patties until crispy, flipping once, about 12 minutes total.. While patties cook, prepare the sauce: Combine mayonnaise, chipotle pepper, adobo sauce, and lemon juice in the bowl of a food processor; process until smooth.. Serve crab cakes with sauce on the side.

name: Poor Man's Crab Cakes
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cold baked potatoes'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced celery'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'imitation crabmeat, flaked and chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh dill'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}
steps: Split and mash the potatoes in a mixing bowl; set aside. The potato skins may be left on if desired.. Melt the butter in a saucepan over medium-high heat; cook and stir the bell pepper, onion, and celery in the melted butter until they begin to soften, 5 to 7 minutes. Remove from heat and stir the milk into the mixture; pour the mixture over the mashed potatoes and stir to combine. The consistency should not be too runny. Allow the mixture to cool completely.. Preheat an oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Add the crabmeat, Cheddar cheese, and dill to the potato mixture; season with salt. Lightly mix. Pour the beaten eggs into the mixture and stir to combine. If the mixture is too thin, bread crumbs or flour can be added to make more firm. Form the mixture into 24 small patties.. Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat; cook the patties in small batches in the skillet until completely browned and crisp, 3 to 5 minutes per side. Do not flip until bottom is fully browned and crisp; this ensures the patties will not break. Transfer to a baking dish in the oven to keep hot until all are cooked. Serve hot.

name: Dorsey's Fish & Oyster House Crab Cakes
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'Old Bay Seasoning™'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'biscuit baking mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dried parsley'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'prepared mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'crabmeat'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'quarts', 'name': 'vegetable oil for frying'}
steps: Mix together Old Bay™ seasoning, baking mix, and parsley in a medium size mixing bowl. Stir mayonnaise, mustard, egg, and Worcestershire sauce into dry ingredients. Mix in crab meat gently. Form mixture into 6 to 8 balls.. Heat 1 inch oil in a large, heavy bottomed skillet to 365 degrees F (185 degrees C). Place balls in pan, and flatten slightly with a spatula. Flip the crab cakes over after 3 minutes, or when the crab cake is browned on one side. Continue frying until done. Drain on paper towels.

name: Air Fryer Cajun Crab Cakes
ingredients: {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Cajun seasoning'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground white pepper (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'fresh lump crabmeat'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'remoulade sauce, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'brioche slider buns (Optional)'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 370 degrees F (188 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions.. Mix bread crumbs, mayonnaise, egg, Worcestershire, mustard, Cajun seasoning, salt, cayenne, and pepper together in a small mixing bowl. Fold in crabmeat gently.. Form into 3 equal-size crab cakes using a biscuit cutter. Place cakes on a parchment round and transfer to the air fryer basket.. Cook in the preheated air fryer for 6 minutes. Flip and continue to cook until browned, about 6 minutes more. Serve with remoulade sauce on slider buns.

name: Laura's Maryland Crab Cakes
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dried parsley flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'seafood seasoning (such as Old Bay®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'white bread, crusts removed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'fresh crabmeat'}
steps: Mix egg, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise, parsley, seafood seasoning, baking powder, and salt together with your hands in a large mixing bowl. Tear bread into tiny bits; add to the egg mixture. Gently fold in crabmeat; form into 4 cakes and arrange onto a lined baking sheet.. Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Bake crab cakes until heated through and lightly browned, about 30 minutes.

name: Mini Crab Cakes with Curried Tartar Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'relish'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'spicy mustard'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'hot sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garam masala'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'minced cilantro'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'salted butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'red bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'green bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'fresh bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'crabmeat'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'seafood seasoning (such as Old Bay®)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil for frying, or as needed'}
steps: Mix mayonnaise, relish, mustard, hot sauce, garam masala, and cilantro for tartar sauce in a bowl until well blended. Cover and chill in the refrigerator until flavors have blended, about 1 hour.. Melt butter in a frying pan. Add celery, onion, and bell peppers; saute until soft, about 5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and set aside to cool.. Place bread crumbs and crabmeat in a large bowl. Add cooled vegetables, eggs, seafood seasoning, pepper, and cayenne; mix until well blended and moist. Form crab mixture into 1 1/2- to 2-inch balls.. Heat oil in a frying pan over medium or medium-low heat. Add crab balls and flatten the tops with a spatula. Fry to a golden brown, about 5 minutes. Carefully flip and repeat to brown the other side. Drain on a wire rack.. Serve with curried tartar sauce.

name: Crab Cakes with Cilantro-Sour Cream Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'minced red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced red onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'fresh crabmeat, well picked over'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'dry bread crumbs, divided'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Sauce:'}, {'quantity': '1 ⅓', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'sour cream, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'minced red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'finely chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'corn oil for frying'}
steps: Put eggs, lemon juice, mayonnaise, bell pepper, onion, cilantro, salt, cayenne pepper, and black pepper in a mixing bowl and mix well. Gently fold in crabmeat and 1/2 of the bread crumbs.. Form crabmeat mixture into 8 patties. Coat both sides in remaining bread crumbs. Place patties on waxed paper and freeze for 15 minutes.. Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Prepare the sauce: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, bell pepper, garlic, lemon juice, cilantro, and cayenne pepper together in a bowl. Season with salt and black pepper.. Heat 1/2 of the oil in a skillet over medium heat. Carefully add patties to hot oil in batches. Fry until golden, about 30 seconds on each side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate to drain. Repeat with remaining patties, adding remaining oil as needed.. Transfer patties to a baking sheet and bake in the preheated oven for 10 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center of a patty should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Serve patties with sauce.

name: Easy Fried Crab Cakes
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(4 ounce) packet', 'name': 'saltine crackers, crushed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'bell pepper, minced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'green onions, white parts only, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Dijon mustard, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'cooked blue crabmeat, drained'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'seafood seasoning (such as Old Bay®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Italian-seasoned bread crumbs, or more as needed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'canola oil, or more as needed'}
steps: Mix crushed crackers, bell pepper, green onions, egg, mayonnaise, and Dijon together in a large bowl. Gently fold in crabmeat, seafood seasoning, and black pepper using a wooden spoon or spatula. Form crabmeat mixture into 1/2-inch-thick patties, 2 to 3 inches in diameter.. Put bread crumbs on a plate. Coat patties with bread crumbs.. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add patties in batches and cook until golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes on each side. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towels. Repeat with remaining patties, adding more oil as needed.

name: Crushed Pretzel Crab Cakes
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, divided'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'crushed pretzels'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 ounce) can', 'name': 'crabmeat'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'jumbo', 'name': 'egg'}
steps: Heat 3 tablespoons butter in a skillet over medium-high heat. Saute onion in the hot butter until soft, 5 to 7 minutes. Set aside.. Mix crushed pretzels, garlic powder, paprika, and pepper together in a bowl. Add crabmeat and egg, followed by onion. Mix together and form into small, palm-size patties.. Melt remaining butter in a pan over medium-high heat. Cook the patties until golden brown, about 4 minutes per side. Serve.

name: Fabienne's 'Black-Eyed' Crab Cakes
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'lemon', 'name': 'lemon, zested'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'mustard powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'seafood seasoning (such as Old Bay®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rinsed and drained canned black-eyed peas'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) can', 'name': 'crab meat, drained and chunked'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}
steps: Whisk lemon zest, mustard powder, seafood seasoning, onion powder, and cayenne pepper together in a bowl. Add black-eyed peas to lemon zest mixture and smash with a fork until mixture is crumbly. Stir egg and mayonnaise into pea mixture; gently fold in crab meat and Parmesan cheese until combined.. Form pea mixture into 5-ounce patties. Pour bread crumbs into a shallow bowl and press patties into bread crumbs, coating both sides. Place patties on a plate and refrigerate until chilled, at least 30 minutes.. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat; fry patties until golden brown, about 4 minutes per side.
